  "description": [
    "Friday 8 September 1961 MODERN NUCLEAR POWER The above In an artists conception of the modern nuclearpowered cruiser USS IXNG REACH tiring a polar missile at sea LONG BEACH will join the U S fleet tomorrow during commissioning exercises at the South Annex of the Boston Naval Shipyard First Major Nuclear Surface Ship Completes Sea Trials Joins Fleet The world s first major nuclear powered surface ship the guided missile cruiser USS LONG REACH will join the U S fleet tomorrow during commissioning ceremonies at the South Annex of the Boston Naval Shipyard at 1430 Principal speaker for the event will be the Honorable John B Connally Jr Secretary of the Navy who will address the 6000 invited guests and the LONG BEACH crew of 60 officers and 900 men A 14200ton cruiser LONG BEACH was constructed by the Bethlehem Steel Com panys Quincy Shipyard Quincy Mass her keel laid on 2 Dec 1957 First Skipper The 721foot vessel will be commanded by APT Eugene P Wilkinson He was also first commanding officer of the nuclear powered submarine USS NAUT ILUS the U S Navys first nu clear powered ship Built at a cost of 320million dollars LONG BEACH is"
  ],
